[1] Case updates
- Mon 16 Sep 2019. CMRE update
[CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola), machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.dropbox.com/s/n13m4tszrwrr06j/CMRE_Bulletin%20Ebola%20du%2015%20septembre%202019.pdf?dl=0&fbclid=IwAR3Psy8byGDoXLW9cuLk67fOMqK4WR-ANbDDqdnLIFNP0INzTmnlRhXGFCw

Epidemiological situation in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri on 15 Sep 2019:
Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3128, of which 3017 are confirmed and 111 probable. In total, there have been 2095 deaths (1984 confirmed and 111 probable) and 948 people recovered.
- 475 suspected cases are under investigation;
- 9 new confirmed cases, including 5 in North Kivu -- 1 each in Beni, Katwa, Kayna, Kalunguta, and Oicha; 4 in Ituri in Mandima;
- 5 new confirmed deaths, including 1 community death in Oicha in North Kivu; 4 deaths in the Ebola treatment centers (ETCs): 3 in North Kivu, notably 1 each Butembo, Mabalako, and Katwa; also 1 in Ituri in Komanda;
- 3 recovered people released from ETCs in North Kivu, including 2 in Butembo and 1 in Beni;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 159 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

Vaccination: Since initiation of vaccinations on 8 Aug [2018], 220 529 people vaccinated.

Surveillance at entry points: 95 243 255 individuals. There are currently 98 points of entry being monitored.

