- Thu 12 Sep 2019. African Union volunteers
[Actu 30, in French, trans., abridged, edited]
https://actu30.info/2019/09/12/rdc-20-volontaires-de-lunion-africaine-formes-pour-renforcer-les-operations-de-lutte-contre-ebola/

In total, 20 volunteers from the African Union (AU) were trained on the tasks to be performed in the fight against Ebola virus disease in the DRC, on [Wed 11 Sep 2019] in Kinshasa. These are 7 infection prevention and control officers, a laboratory technician, a logistician and a data manager, and 10 epidemiologists.

This number is in addition to the 37 already deployed by the African Union in the east of the country, where this epidemic is rife.

These volunteers were guided and briefed on the issues and challenges that await them in the provinces attacked by Ebola, including those in North Kivu, South Kivu and Ituri. And this, in order to strengthen the response operations against this virus.

It should be noted that this training was provided by Africa CDC, a technical institution of the African Union to help Member States respond quickly and effectively to the threat of disease.

